<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Carlow University</h2>
<strong>Pittsburgh, PA</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>The student who has taken college level courses in one or more subjects in high school and has submitted the results of the College Board Advanced Placement (AP) Exams will be considered for advanced placement. Exam scores of 3, 4 or 5 may entitle the student to academic credit in course areas corresponding to the advanced study. Scores are submitted to the Admissions Office, usually at the time of application for admission.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://admissions.carlow.edu/undergrad-transfer/adm-proc/advplace-proc.html" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

